Microbial agents associated with pneumonia in children from Uruguay. The etiology of severe pneumonia, not frequently encountered in a community-based study, was determined in 204 hospitalized children less than 5 years of age. Potential pathogens were identified in 41% of episodes. Viruses were isolated or antigen was detected in 36.3% of cases 82.4% of these cases were due to respiratory syncytial virus. Bacteria or bacterial antigens were identified in 13.2% of cases